# **Exercise 2.6 – Unsafe Control Actions (UCAs)**

| ID    | Controller      | Control Action | UCA Type          | Hazard(s) | Unsafe Scenario                                    |
| ----- | --------------- | -------------- | ----------------- | --------- | -------------------------------------------------- |
| UCA-1 | Planning Module | Brake command  | Not provided      | H-1, H-2  | Pedestrian/vehicle present but no braking occurs   |
| UCA-2 | Planning Module | Brake command  | Provided unsafely | H-4       | Braking occurs without real obstacle               |
| UCA-3 | Planning Module | Brake command  | Wrong timing      | H-1, H-2  | Braking occurs too late to avoid collision         |
| UCA-4 | Planning Module | Brake command  | Wrong duration    | H-4       | Braking continues longer than necessary            |
| UCA-5 | Human Operator  | Override       | Not provided      | H-5       | Operator fails to intervene in dangerous situation |
| UCA-6 | Human Operator  | Override       | Provided unsafely | H-4       | Operator overrides system unnecessarily            |
| UCA-7 | Human Operator  | Override       | Wrong timing      | H-5       | Intervention happens too late                      |
| UCA-8 | Human Operator  | Override       | Wrong duration    | H-4       | Override lasts longer than needed                  |

