# **Exercise 2.7 – Safety Constraints**

| UCA   | Safety Constraint                                                    | Level        | Verification          |
| ----- | -------------------------------------------------------------------- | ------------ | --------------------- |
| UCA-1 | System must ensure obstacle detection before brake decisions         | System-level | Simulation testing    |
| UCA-2 | Braking must only trigger when obstacle confidence exceeds threshold | Model-level  | Model evaluation      |
| UCA-3 | Perception-to-action delay must be below safety threshold            | System-level | Timing analysis       |
| UCA-4 | Braking must stop once hazard is removed                             | System-level | Scenario testing      |
| UCA-5 | Human operator must actively monitor system during operation         | System-level | Operational procedure |
| UCA-6 | Overrides must only be triggered in verified hazardous conditions    | System-level | Testing + validation  |
| UCA-7 | System must alert operator during uncertainty or hazard conditions   | System-level | System testing        |
| UCA-8 | Control must automatically return to normal mode after override      | System-level | Integration testing   |

