# **Exercise 2.8 – Causal Loss Scenarios**

| UCA   | Causal Scenario                                        | Root Cause                          | Related Constraint              |
| ----- | ------------------------------------------------------ | ----------------------------------- | ------------------------------- |
| UCA-1 | Obstacle exists but perception fails to detect it      | Sensor limitations or model failure | Obstacle detection requirement  |
| UCA-2 | False detection triggers unnecessary braking           | Perception error or noise           | Confidence threshold constraint |
| UCA-3 | Delayed perception or processing leads to late braking | System latency                      | Timing constraint               |
| UCA-4 | Planner does not stop braking after hazard disappears  | Stale perception feedback           | Brake stop condition            |
| UCA-5 | Operator is distracted or fatigued and misses hazard   | Human attention limitation          | Monitoring requirement          |
| UCA-6 | Operator misinterprets normal situation as dangerous   | Human error                         | Override validation constraint  |
| UCA-7 | Operator reacts too slowly                             | Reaction time delay                 | Alerting requirement            |
| UCA-8 | Operator forgets to release override                   | Mode confusion                      | Automatic reset constraint      |

